By default, JPA doesn&#39;t natively support enum types. When you update an entity, JPA will not detect changes to enum fields. As a result, it might treat any change to an enum attribute as a new insert rather than an update.

To properly handle enum attributes in JPA, you should use the @Enumerated annotation to specify how enum types should be stored in the database. The @Enumerated annotation allows you to define whether the enum should be stored as a string or an integer.

Here&#39;s an example of how to use @Enumerated:

    @Entity
    public class Book {
        // ...
        @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING) // Store the enum as a string
        private Type type;
        // ...
    }

