            &lt;env-entry-type&gt;java.lang.Long&lt;/env-entry-type&gt;
            &lt;env-entry-value&gt;42&lt;/env-entry-value&gt;
        &lt;/env-entry&gt;

    &lt;/web-app&gt;



Envivorment entries are fully available from spring context.

    @Configuration
    public class UniverseConfiguration {

        @Profile(&quot;universe&quot;)
        @Value(&quot;${answer}&quot;)
        Long answer;
    
    }

In short, web.xml isn&#39;t deprecated and removed. It is just that with ServletInitalizers it isn&#39;t required anymore. During application bootstrap, webServer will still scan for web.xml.

